law.text:
As used in KRS 65.310 to 65.314:
"Public entity" means any organization that represents a statewide association of local governments where the majority of its governing body is composed of mayors, county judges/executive, or other local elected officials, and whose membership includes any or a combination of the following:
Cities;
Counties;
Charter counties;
Urban-counties;
Consolidated local governments; and
Unified local governments; and
"Affiliated organization" means any incorporated or unincorporated organization staffed, managed, or administered by a public entity.
